<?xml version="1.0"?>
<!-- 
Internal Map:

The Map is a set of rectangular sectors which define the Area that is accessible by the walker. 
x0-m is the forward edge, x1-m is the rear edge. y0-m is right, y1-m is left. z1-m is the floor level, z0-m is the heigth. 
Doorways are sectors too, but they are only passable when the specified property is 1 (e.g. the door is open).

Sectors can have types, e.g. Stairways or sloped sectors can have type 1 or 2, which means they are sloped in x or y direction


When creating the Map, ensure that x0-m, y0-m and z0-m values are the numeric greater ones. Remember -1 is greater than -2.

Left, below, forward from Origin is negative, right, up, rear is positive.

Sector types:
  1 - sloped in x direction
  2 - sloped in y direction
  3 - trap door/portal, needs <target> to specify the index of the target sector
  4 - elevator, needs <target> to specify the index of the target sector and <pos-norm> to know where the elevator floor is
-->

